The '''Fabyan Windmill''' is an authentic, working [[Architecture of the Netherlands|Dutch]] [[windmill]] dating from the 1850s located in [[Geneva, Illinois]]. The {{convert|68|ft|m}}, five-[[Storey|story]] [[wood]]en [[smock mill]] sits upon the onetime estate of Colonel [[George Fabyan]], but is now part of the [[Kane County, Illinois|Kane County]] [[Nature reserve|Forest Preserve]] District.

In 1979, the windmill was listed on the [[National Register of Historic Places]]. The following year, the windmill was selected to be on a [[Postage stamps and postal history of the United States|U.S. postage stamp]] as part of a series of five American windmills included in a stamp booklet called "WINDMILLS USA".<ref name="KCForestPreserve">{{cite web
