==History==
During the mid-19th century, the Fabyan Windmill was constructed by [[Germans|German]] craftsmen, Louis Blackhaus,<ref name="KCForestPreserve"/> and his brother-in-law Freidrick Brockmann, on a site at Meyers Road near 16th Street in [[York Township, DuPage County, Illinois|York Township]] between [[Elmhurst, Illinois|Elmhurst]] and [[Oak Brook, Illinois]] (now [[Lombard, Illinois]]).<ref name="FabyanWindmillBrochure"/><ref name="FabyanLegacy">{{Cite book
  | last1 = Larson
  | first1 = Darlene
  | last2 = Hiebert
  | first2 = Laurie
  | contribution = The Fabyan Legacy
  | editor1-last = Ehresmann
  | editor1-first = Julia M.
  | editor2-last = 
  | editor2-first = 
  | title = Geneva, Illinois:  A History of Its Times and Places
  | volume = 
  | pages = 170<U+2013>172
  | publisher = Geneva Public Library District
  | place = [[Geneva, Illinois]]
  | year = 1977
  | isbn = LOC 77-087991
  | url =  
  | contribution-url =    
  | accessdate =
  | postscript = <!--None-->  }}</ref><ref name="GenevaPostcards">{{cite book
  | last = Laukaitis
  | first = John J.
  | authorlink = 
  | coauthors = 
